          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-09 19:42:34" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cause a fire to be extinguished</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to extinguish a fire</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to put out a fire</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>‘To put out fierce fires’ may be expressed as ‘to cause fierce fires no longer to burn’ or ‘to make large fires stop burning.’ In order to speak of ‘fierce fires’ it may be necessary in some languages to speak of ‘large, hot fires.’</Comments>
