          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-09 19:42:34" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cease burning, either because of lack of material to be burned or because the fire has been forcibly extinguished</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to stop burning</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The expression ‘our lamps are going out’ may be rendered as ‘our lamps will soon not be burning’ or ‘our lamps will burn only a little bit more.’ It may, however, be misleading to speak of ‘lamps burning’ (see discussion in {D:14.65}), and accordingly, it may be much better to translate ‘our lamps will show light only a little bit more’ or ‘the oil in our lamps will burn only a little bit more.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
